l_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first opponent on the schedule is Team Germany, last summer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s World Cup champions, on July 27 followed by France (July 30) and the winner of the Olympic Qualifying Tournament (Aug. 2).\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999967103577, \"rank\": 3.2876205333427712e-09, \"text\": \"Team Germany\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1461, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999607097326535, \"rank\": 3.927863624604519e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hachimura is likely to play in his second Olympic Games just months removed from the best statistical season of his NBA career.\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.026069157397085e-29, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 6-foot-8 forward averaged 13.6 points (most since 2020-21) while shooting 53.7% from the field (career-best) and 42.2% from 3-point range (on 3.4 attempts per game, both career-highs) in 68 games played, including 39 starts.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Lakers went 22-10 to end the regular season with Hachimura in the starting lineup, as he averaged 15.9 points and 5.1 rebounds while shooting 57.6% from the floor and 44.4% from downtown in that span.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 2020 Olympics, Hachimura put up 22.3 points and 6.7 rebounds per game, though Team Japan failed to win a game and finished 11th out of 12 places in the final standings.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}, {\"begin\": 2189, \"end\": 2199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.262458499701942e-13, \"text\": \"Team Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hachimura is expected to be one of many former Zags who\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll compete for the gold medal this summer.\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2281, \"end\": 2290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrew Nembhard and Kelly Olynyk are part of a loaded Team Canada squad, while Filip Petrusev is set to compete for one of Team Serbia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 12 roster spots.\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Nembhard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Nembhard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Nembhard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Nembhard\"}, {\"begin\": 2408, \"end\": 2414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olynyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\"}, {\"begin\": 2436, \"end\": 2447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9936784446108536, \"rank\": 0.006361489094216049, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filip_Petru\\u0161ev\", \"score\": 0.9999999262890951, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filip Petrusev\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filip_Pet